atures" style="width: 100%!important;"></a></p><p style="padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;">		<div class="elementor elementor-86504">\n			<div class="elementor-inner">\n				<div class="elementor-section-wrap">\n							<section data-id="44eb990f" class="elementor-element elementor-element-44eb990f elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default elementor-section elementor-top-section" data-element_type="section">\n						<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">\n				<div class="elementor-row">\n				<div data-id="273afadb" class="elementor-element elementor-element-273afadb elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column" data-element_type="column">\n			<div class="elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated">\n					<div class="elementor-widget-wrap">\n				<div data-id="18382a3d" class="elementor-element elementor-element-18382a3d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="text-editor.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n					<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">Some months have passed since the last big update, I hope you will enjoy all the new WooCommerce features of this release. The goal of this update is to increase conversion of your shop and having a beautiful and professional design.</div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</section>\n				<section data-id="55ad8806" class="elementor-element elementor-element-55ad8806 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default elementor-section elementor-top-section" data-element_type="section">\n						<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">\n				<div class="elementor-row">\n				<div data-id="3406741f" class="elementor-element elementor-element-3406741f elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column" data-element_type="column">\n			<div class="elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated">\n					<div class="elementor-widget-wrap">\n				<div data-id="5d42ee3b" class="elementor-element elementor-element-5d42ee3b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-element_type="heading.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n			<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Cart Icon Shortcode</h3>		</div>\n				</div>\n				<div data-id="7202bee2" class="elementor-element elementor-element-7202bee2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="text-editor.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n					<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">Many users asked for this new feature. Now you can display the cart icon with the <strong></strong> shortcode. Check all the available parameters here: <a href="https://docs.oceanwp.org/article/502-oceanwpwoocart-shortcode" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://docs.oceanwp.org/article/502-oceanwpwoocart-shortcode</a></div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n				<div data-id="265d4fa7" class="elementor-element elementor-element-265d4fa7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="text-editor.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n					<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix"><p>With this shortcode, you can create any type of header and place the cart icon where you want. Here is a little example:</p></div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n				<div data-id="68f9698d" class="elementor-element elementor-element-68f9698d elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-element_type="image.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n					<div class="elementor-image">\n											<a href="https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cart-icon.png" data-elementor-open-lightbox="default">\n							<img width="1024" height="100" src="https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cart-icon.png" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="" srcset="https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cart-icon.png 1024w, https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cart-icon-300x29.png 300w, https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cart-icon-768x75.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" />								</a>\n											</div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</section>\n				<section data-id="f140a8c" class="elementor-element elementor-element-f140a8c elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default elementor-section elementor-top-section" data-element_type="section">\n						<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">\n				<div class="elementor-row">\n				<div data-id="f5d602e" class="elementor-element elementor-element-f5d602e elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column" data-element_type="column">\n			<div class="elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated">\n					<div class="elementor-widget-wrap">\n				<div data-id="dd4879b" class="elementor-element elementor-element-dd4879b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="text-editor.default">\n				<div class="elementor-widget-container">\n					<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix"><p>You can see that the cart icon style is completely different than the cart icon from the navigation. It&#8217;s done this way, because some options are complicated to add in the shortcode, so I created an independent style to make everything to work smoothly.</p></div>\n				</div>\n				</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n						</div>\n			</div>\n		</section>\n				<section data-id="657d5665" class="elementor-element elementor-element-657d5665 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default elementor-section elementor-top-section" data-element_type="section">\n						<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">\n				<div class="elementor-row">\n				<div data-id